[{"id":"VH979782","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents 2 reservoirs connected by a horizontal metal rod of length L. The reservoir on the left contains a hot liquid at 100 degrees Celsius and the reservoir on the right contains an ice bath at 0 degrees Celsius.\" height=\"78\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979782.g01.png\" width=\"485\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A student wants to compare the thermal conductivities of several metal rods with different lengths <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and cross-sectional areas <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The student connects each rod to two reservoirs, one containing a hot liquid at temperature <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"100 degrees Celsius \"><math alttext=\"100 degrees Celsius \" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>100</mn><mi>°</mi><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and the other containing an ice bath at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 degrees Celsius \"><math alttext=\"0 degrees Celsius \" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0</mn><mi>°</mi><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. Each rod is kept in contact with the reservoirs for the same fixed time interval <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta lowercase t\"><math alttext=\"delta lowercase t\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> be the amount of energy transferred through a rod in the time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta lowercase t\"><math alttext=\"delta lowercase t\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following lists all the additional quantities that must be measured to be able to compare the thermal conductivities?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979782_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]